Overview
Automate Quality Control (DocVu)
• Automate the Quality Check & Control for OCR extracted documents from DocVu.
• Consolidate Quality data into the Spectr database for improved accessibility, search and 
analysis.
An Azure Functions based CI/CD pipeline that performs:
• Data Ingestion & Transformation: Ingests a batch of extracted OCR policy data via 
JSON records
• Quality Checks: Automate the checking of keys / fields against the Ground Truth
• Quality Approval: Based on developed QC rules and results
• Data Sampling: Use advance statistics-based sampling methods to sample the batch
• Generates Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) report : Enhances the quality check using 
manual intervention
Statistics:
- Total 17 batches of records data processed
- ~225000 policies' data processed along with generated HITL team report.

Overview
VAX AIM
Project aims to:
• Migrate legacy policy data containing Owner and Lender Policy information from VAX AIM 
system. 
• Transform & consolidate data into the centralized database for improved accessibility, 
search and analysis.
AI team is to develop a data pipeline that performs:
• Data Extraction: Retrieve data from the VAX AIM system.
• Data Validation: Ensure data integrity and consistency
• Data Transformation: Cleanse, transform, and format the extracted data to ensure
compatibility with the schema and mapping provided by the business.
• Data Sampling: Use advance statistics-based sampling methods to sample the batch
• Generate Full report and subset report: Produce different output files
• Around 800,000 policies data processed, extracted and approved with the help of HITL 
team.

Overview
Steps AI
Project aims to:
• Identify duplicates using semantics and keyword search and help employees in 
identifying duplicates in a more efficient manner
Process:
• No api call or security issues
• The algorithm incorporates a multi-stepped approach to efficiently identify duplicates:
• Embedding Generation: We create embeddings for all records using a transformer-based 
model to capture semantic similarities.
• FAISS-Based Similarity Search: To quickly identify potential duplicate pairs, we employ 
the FAISS algorithm to retrieve records with high similarity scores, since it is an efficient 
similarity search using clusters of dense vectors.
• Refined Similarity Search: We apply two additional filters to further refine the duplicate 
identification process and ensure accurate classification.
